caption: The quintessential neighborhood pub. Great pizza, great wings, great atmosphere. Been going here for 25 years.

Stopped by for a brew and a late dinner. Female bartender was very friendly and was passionate about some of her favorites. (Reuben Rolls, Wings...) Also said about the burgers so we got two and an order of wings.  Burgers were great, wings were meaty but the medium wing sauce needed more flavor.  Two cold brews were great while we were waiting for the carry out.  Yuengling was frosty and a freaky beer was good too. Looking forward to our next visit Friday for their Fish and Chips!  Thanks and enjoy as I recommend patronizing this local favorite. KC

Fantastic portions and delicious food. We had the burger special, the chicken sandwich, a kids meal and the banana pudding. They also have the NFL Sunday ticket but have several TVs that are blue from overuse.  A long standing establishment that has been refreshed with better food without losing the nostalgic touch.

Nice local place! Went at 12noon on a Saturday during March Madness. The bar was packed, but my family was able to get a table in the dining room with no wait. The restaurant was medium volume; not too loud, but also not too quiet that my 4yo was a nuisance. I had a cheeseburger, true medium with a pink center. The (brioche?) bun was a little burnt but was still very yummy. My husband and son shared a medium pizza, and both loved it! The pepperoni is especially fun because it's just one large pepperoni per pizza slice vs. many small slices. So glad we tried it, we will return!
